name: assetTurnoverTTM
description: Measures the efficiency of a company in generating sales from its assets. It indicates how well a company is utilizing its assets to generate revenue.

name: capitalExpenditureCoverageRatioTTM
description: Measures a company's ability to generate enough cash flow to cover its capital expenditures. It indicates the company's ability to fund its investments in fixed assets.

name: cashConversionCycleTTM
description: Measures the time it takes for a company to convert its investments in inventory and other resources into cash flows from sales. It indicates the efficiency of a company's working capital management.

name: cashFlowCoverageRatiosTTM
description: Measures a company's ability to generate enough cash flow to cover its financial obligations, such as interest payments and debt repayments. It indicates the company's ability to meet its financial obligations.

name: cashFlowToDebtRatioTTM
description: Measures a company's ability to generate cash flow from its operations relative to its total debt. It indicates the company's ability to generate enough cash flow to service its debt.

name: cashPerShareTTM
description: Measures the amount of cash available to common shareholders per share of common stock. It indicates the liquidity position of a company and its ability to distribute cash to shareholders.

name: cashRatioTTM
description: Measures a company's ability to cover its short-term liabilities with its cash and cash equivalents. It indicates the liquidity position of a company and its ability to meet its short-term obligations.

name: companyEquityMultiplierTTM
description: Measures the proportion of a company's total assets that are financed by its shareholders' equity. It indicates the extent to which a company relies on equity financing compared to debt financing.

name: currentRatioTTM
description: Measures a company's ability to cover its short-term liabilities with its short-term assets. It indicates the liquidity position of a company and its ability to meet its short-term obligations.

name: daysOfInventoryOutstandingTTM
description: Measures the average number of days it takes for a company to sell its inventory. It indicates the efficiency of a company's inventory management and the speed at which it can convert inventory into sales.

name: daysOfPayablesOutstandingTTM
description: Measures the average number of days it takes for a company to pay its suppliers. It indicates the efficiency of a company's accounts payable management and the time it takes to settle its payables.

name: daysOfSalesOutstandingTTM
description: Measures the average number of days it takes for a company to collect payment from its customers. It indicates the efficiency of a company's accounts receivable management and the time it takes to convert sales into cash.

name: debtEquityRatioTTM
description: Measures the proportion of a company's total debt to its shareholders' equity. It indicates the extent to which a company relies on debt financing compared to equity financing.

name: debtRatioTTM
description: Measures the proportion of a company's total assets that are financed by debt. It indicates the extent to which a company relies on debt financing compared to equity financing.

name: dividendPaidAndCapexCoverageRatioTTM
description: Measures a company's ability to generate enough cash flow to cover its dividend payments and capital expenditures. It indicates the company's ability to fund its dividend payments and investments in fixed assets.

name: dividendYielTTM
description: Measures the dividend income generated by an investment relative to its market price. It indicates the return on investment from dividends received.

name: ebitPerRevenueTTM
description: Measures a company's operating profitability as a percentage of its revenue. It indicates the company's ability to generate operating profit from its revenue.

name: ebtPerEbitTTM
description: Measures a company's ability to generate earnings before taxes (EBT) relative to its earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT). It indicates the company's ability to generate earnings before taxes from its operating profit.

name: effectiveTaxRateTTM
description: Measures the proportion of a company's pre-tax income that is paid in taxes. It indicates the company's tax efficiency and the impact of taxes on its profitability.

name: enterpriseValueMultipleTTM
description: Measures the ratio of a company's enterprise value to its earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization (EBITDA). It indicates the valuation of a company relative to its EBITDA.

name: fixedAssetTurnoverTTM
description: Measures the efficiency of a company in generating sales from its fixed assets. It indicates how well a company is utilizing its fixed assets to generate revenue.

name: freeCashFlowOperatingCashFlowRatioTTM
description: Measures the proportion of a company's operating cash flow that is available for discretionary purposes after deducting capital expenditures. It indicates the company's ability to generate free cash flow from its operating activities.

name: freeCashFlowPerShareTTM
description: Measures the amount of free cash flow available to common shareholders per share of common stock. It indicates the cash flow generated by a company that is available to distribute to shareholders after deducting capital expenditures.

name: grossProfitMarginTTM
description: Measures a company's gross profit as a percentage of its revenue. It indicates the company's ability to generate profit from its revenue after deducting the cost of goods sold.

name: interestCoverageTTM
description: Measures a company's ability to cover its interest expenses with its operating income. It indicates the company's ability to meet its interest obligations from its operating profit.

name: inventoryTurnoverTTM
description: Measures the number of times a company's inventory is sold and replaced during a specific period. It indicates the efficiency of a company's inventory management and the speed at which it can convert inventory into sales.

name: longTermDebtToCapitalizationTTM
description: Measures the proportion of a company's long-term debt to its total capitalization. It indicates the extent to which a company relies on long-term debt financing compared to equity financing.

name: netIncomePerEBTTTM
description: Measures a company's net income as a percentage of its earnings before taxes (EBT). It indicates the company's ability to generate net income from its pre-tax earnings.

name: netProfitMarginTTM
description: Measures a company's net income as a percentage of its revenue. It indicates the company's ability to generate profit from its revenue after deducting all expenses and taxes.

name: operatingCashFlowPerShareTTM
description: Measures the amount of operating cash flow available to common shareholders per share of common stock. It indicates the cash flow generated by a company's operating activities that is available to distribute to shareholders.

name: operatingCashFlowSalesRatioTTM
description: Measures a company's operating cash flow as a percentage of its revenue. It indicates the company's ability to generate cash flow from its operating activities relative to its revenue.

name: operatingCycleTTM
description: Measures the average number of days it takes for a company to convert its investments in inventory and accounts receivable into cash flows from sales. It indicates the efficiency of a company's working capital management and the time it takes to convert its investments into cash.

name: operatingProfitMarginTTM
description: Measures a company's operating profit as a percentage of its revenue. It indicates the company's ability to generate profit from its revenue after deducting all operating expenses.

name: payablesTurnoverTTM
description: Measures the number of times a company pays its suppliers during a specific period. It indicates the efficiency of a company's accounts payable management and the speed at which it settles its payables.

name: payoutRatioTTM
description: Measures the proportion of a company's earnings that is paid out as dividends to its shareholders. It indicates the portion of a company's earnings that is distributed to shareholders as cash dividends.

name: pretaxProfitMarginTTM
description: Measures a company's pre-tax profit as a percentage of its revenue. It indicates the company's ability to generate profit from its revenue before deducting taxes.

name: priceBookValueRatioTTM
description: Measures the ratio of a company's market price per share to its book value per share. It indicates the valuation of a company relative to its book value.

name: priceCashFlowRatioTTM
description: Measures the ratio of a company's market price per share to its cash flow per share. It indicates the valuation of a company relative to its cash flow.

name: priceEarningsRatioTTM
description: Measures the ratio of a company's market price per share to its earnings per share. It indicates the valuation of a company relative to its earnings.

name: priceEarningsToGrowthRatioTTM
description: Measures the ratio of a company's price-earnings (P/E) ratio to its earnings growth rate. It indicates the valuation of a company relative to its earnings growth potential.

name: priceFairValueTTM
description: Measures the ratio of a company's market price per share to its fair value per share. It indicates the valuation of a company relative to its fair value.

name: priceSalesRatioTTM
description: Measures the ratio of a company's market price per share to its revenue per share. It indicates the valuation of a company relative to its revenue.

name: priceToBookRatioTTM
description: Measures the ratio of a company's market price per share to its book value per share. It indicates the valuation of a company relative to its book value.

name: priceToFreeCashFlowsRatioTTM
description: Measures the ratio of a company's market price per share to its free cash flow per share. It indicates the valuation of a company relative to its free cash flow.

name: priceToOperatingCashFlowsRatioTTM
description: Measures the ratio of a company's market price per share to its operating cash flow per share. It indicates the valuation of a company relative to its operating cash flow.

name: priceToSalesRatioTTM
description: Measures the ratio of a company's market price per share to its revenue per share. It indicates the valuation of a company relative to its revenue.

name: quickRatioTTM
description: Measures a company's ability to cover its short-term liabilities with its quick assets, which include cash, cash equivalents, and accounts receivable. It indicates the liquidity position of a company and its ability to meet its short-term obligations without relying on inventory.

name: receivablesTurnoverTTM
description: Measures the number of times a company collects payment from its customers during a specific period. It indicates the efficiency of a company's accounts receivable management and the speed at which it converts sales into cash.

name: returnOnAssetsTTM
description: Measures a company's profitability relative to its total assets. It indicates the company's ability to generate profit from its assets.

name: returnOnCapitalEmployedTTM
description: Measures a company's profitability relative to its capital employed, which includes both equity and debt financing. It indicates the company's ability to generate profit from its total capital.

name: returnOnEquityTTM
description: Measures a company's profitability relative to its shareholders' equity. It indicates the company's ability to generate profit from its shareholders' investment.

name: shortTermCoverageRatiosTTM
description: Measures a company's ability to cover its short-term liabilities with its short-term assets. It indicates the liquidity position of a company and its ability to meet its short-term obligations.

name: totalDebtToCapitalizationTTM
description: Measures the proportion of a company's total debt to its total capitalization. It indicates the extent to which a company relies on debt financing compared to equity financing.
